events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 44 points despite missing part of the third quarter with an apparent injury, and the New York Knicks beat the Milwaukee Bucks 140-106 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Brunson scores 44 points as the Knicks rout the Bucks 140-106

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook had 21 points, 10 rebounds and seven assists and Nikola Jokic added 19 points, 18 rebounds and nine assists as the Denver Nuggets rallied in the fourth quarter to beat the Dallas Mavericks 112-101 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook and Jokic help Nuggets erase double-digit deficit in 112-101 win over Mavericks

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 22 points, 15 rebounds and eight assists, and the Sacramento Kings beat the Chicago Bulls 124-119 on Sunday to extend their season-high win streak to seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis stars as DeRozan and the streaking Kings beat the Bulls 124-119

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 38 points with 11 rebounds and Kristaps Porzingis had 19 points and 11 boards on Sunday as the Boston Celtics overcame the return of Zion Williamson to the New Orleans lineup and beat the Pelicans 120-119.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics withstand return of Zion Williamson and beat Pelicans 120-119

headlines.description: — Andrew Nembhard scored 19 points, Pascal Siakam had 18 points and nine rebounds and the Indiana Pacers ended NBA-leading Cleveland's winning streak at 12 games, beating the Cavaliers 108-93 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers end NBA-leading Cavaliers' winning streak at 12 with 108-93 victory

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony had 27 points, Paolo Banchero scored seven points in the final 1:32 and the Orlando Magic beat the Philadelphia 76ers 104-99 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony and Banchero lead the Magic past the 76ers 104-99

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 16 of his 27 points from the foul line to overcome his worst shooting performance of the season and help the Oklahoma City Thunder to a 136-95 rout of the Washington Wizards on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander overcomes a poor shooting performance and leads Thunder past Wizards 136-95

headlines.description: — Isaiah Collier drove for the go-ahead layup with 2 seconds left to lift the Utah Jazz to a 112-111 overtime victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Isaiah Collier's late layup in OT lifts the Jazz over the Nets 112-111

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 30 points, Kevin Durant added 27 and the Phoenix Suns rallied in the final minutes to beat the Charlotte Hornets 120-113 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 30 points, Durant has 27 as Suns rally to beat the Hornets 120-113
